<font color="#FF0000">PURIFICATION OF OUR THOUGHTS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Aug 12  1:06:07 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Humming Eagle,<br><br>
Not only are the numbers of grey hairs on my head growing larger, but also the total numbers of hairs is getting smaller.  <br><br>
Trials and tribulations are only that, an part of life.  My family is safe. Financially, were are doing okay.  I look at our life here and see that, while not everything is completely like we want it, things could be so much worse...we are not at war (I did not forget your talk of your ancestors--and some of mine--who were grieviously mistreated; I have stopped dividing up the human race, and decided that we all share common bonds). My boys are looking forward to school and college, and I can still make a contribution.  <br><br>
Life has meaning when we feel that there is a contribution to be made, to make someone else happier, healthier, safer and more secure.  <br><br>
You talked about polluting the river, and it's attempts to purify itself.  The pollution of the rivers is an important issue.  I am a very blessed person, as I live near a river which, while suffering pollution, is still close to what it was many years ago.  This is the North Umpqua River.  The South Umpqua River, which meets the North river only a few miles from my home, is now almost empty from irrigation.  It's temperature in the summer has reached 90 degrees.  The South river is dead to the native Salmon and Steelhead runs which happened during summer; but I was up with my boys to Steamboat Creek, off the North Umpqua, yesterday and snorkeled with hundreds of large, native steelhead trout.  Seeing Brian swim with those large fish was wonderful.<br><br>
Why talk about rivers and pollution on these strings?  Because rivers can be analagous to our own internal struggles, and I've seen Vietnam Veterans pollute their own thinking with words of rage, self-doubt, hate and intolerance.  And I have seen them pollute their bodies with drugs and alcohol.  Like the river in life, the mind's river also needs to be purified of these self-destructive thoughts.  Once the mind is clear, a person will cease polluting the body.<br><br>
&quot;Wapola, is to give away.&quot;  This is a very effective means of purifying thoughts.  <br><br>
Many thanks, my brother.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


